  "body": "I'm trying to calculate transaction fee using go-ethereum. For that I'm getting transaction and check gas price and gas to multiply them. But gas price has a wrong value.\r\n\r\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum v1.10.15\r\n\r\n```\r\n\ttx, _, err := client.TransactionByHash(\r\n\t\tcontext.Background(),\r\n\t\tcommon.HexToHash(\"0xdb9cf08df128fba6d8d06a0b98d967939d7509f36956091e3ad498bda4b29907\"))\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\tfmt.Println(\"Gas price:\", tx.GasPrice())\r\n```\r\nOutput:\r\n```\r\nGas price: 172774404731\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut if you look at the transaction on etherscan https://etherscan.io/tx/0xdb9cf08df128fba6d8d06a0b98d967939d7509f36956091e3ad498bda4b29907 you will see that received value is not Gas price (91572854766) but Max gas fee.\r\n\r\nHow to get correct Gas price for transaction?",
